Barcikowo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Dobre Miasto, within Olsztyn County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-east of Dobre Miasto and  north of the regional capital Olsztyn.
Before 1772 the area was part of Kingdom of Poland, and in 1772â€“1945 it belonged to Prussia and Germany (East Prussia).
